description: Cass panics when her cat, Crudley, is mistaken for the cat of the wealthy Emily Crosswhite and is kidnapped during a stay at the vet. If it's known that the kidnappers got the wrong cat, Crudley could be killed! Before the criminal catches on, Cass goes to speak to Emily to ask her to buy them some time. While Emily is sympathetic to her troubles, Gabe, who works as security for the Crosswhite family, is suspicious. He thinks she's a fraud after Emily's money, and he begins investigating Cass!
name: Vol. 1

description: In their quest for Nazi gold, a group of mercenaries find themselves trapped in an underground WW2 Bunker, fighting for their lives as they are confronted by the greatest abomination the world has ever known.
name: OGN

description: Before the Cataclysm. Before the Nightmare. You've played the hit, free-to-play Action RPG Path of Exile. Now see how it all started...Victario Nevalius, the People's Poet of Sarn, never fancied himself a hero. And yet, he now finds himself among the fearsome Karui, negotiating an alliance to oppose the malignant Gemling Thaumatocracy of Emperor Chitus. Can King Kaom defeat Marceus Lioneye? Will Victario survive to pen the tale? And how do these events connect to the horrifying visions that plague Victario's every waking hour? Grinding Gear Games and Dynamite Entertainment present the never-before-told story behind the destruction of Wraeclast. The road to Cataclysm begins in Path of Exile: Origins #1 - The Karui Way!
name: The Karui Way

description:
Collects Steampunk Snow White, Steampunk Cinderella and Steampunk Red Riding Hood. Presenting a an instant classic from Rod Espinosa, creator of The Courageous Princess and Neotopia and Antarctic Press's own master of the new-age fairy tale. This collection of timeless tales has been galvanized and refueled to charge full steam ahead with a new angle on these familiar favorites!

Collects Steampunk Snow White, Steampunk Cinderella and Steampunk Red Riding Hood.
name: Vol. 1

description: Sector Four is the central city-state of the robot controlled territory in a distant future where artificially intelligent robots have removed humans from civilization. The humans, who had become so dependent on their creations are forced to live in remote regions of the world. Their only hope to come out of hiding is a network of robots given artificial empathy who are sympathetic to the human cause. The story focuses on one robot spy who is assigned to the most dangerous place in the robot world and his struggle with the realization that no matter what he does he'll never be more than just a machine.

She is an operative for a special task force unit and the Seeker persona has become a popular icon for the American public. Secretly, she is LeAnn Heywood - a woman who wears the mantle of Seeker proudly for she understands that she is Seeker and Seeker is her. But she's wrong. Before her there was another Seeker...and before that...yet another...and another. There has always been a Seeker. They may look different. They may "serve" different masters...but the role and legacy of Seeker goes back into the fabled past of a land that most don't believe ever existed. LeAnn may be the current Seeker but a former Seeker, Tracy LeMaster is locked up in a mental hospital for her story of being an incarnate of an ancient Atlantean force couldn't possibly be true. But when Tracy LeMaster escapes, she pledges to reclaim the name of Seeker. And there is only one way to do that...she has to kill the Seeker. Collects issues 1-3 and two addtional stories.
name: TPB

description: Sin Eternal is more than just a re-tooling of the immortal classic, Dante's Inferno. It plants itself firmly in the modern world and away from the political crimes that dominated Dante's work. Sin Eternal brings a very basic questioning of a man's faith as he witnesses some of the most horrendous punishments that could be exacted. The story covers the travels of a man who is sent to Hell to examine the various torments and punishments that the sinners of Earth are forced to face each moment of eternity. From the slovenly gluttons to the fates of the suicides, from the heretics to the thieves, a variety of different levels are covered. From the ferry of Charon, this man is taken into the very depths of evil. And all is not as it appears. Collects issues 1-5.
name: TPB

volume.name: Sin Eternal: Return To Dante's Inferno

description:
Luke works as a mailman in Los Angeles and moonlights as a thief - the empty houses on his postal route are rich, easy pickings for him and his friends. Everything goes to plan until one house turns out to be not quite so empty. The situation escalates rapidly, leaving the happy go lucky thieves battling for their lives...

And all because of Tabatha.
name: TPB

description:
To Baldly Go

Meet Joe the janitor. When he gets stressed out, he turns into a bald ninety-pound strongman accidentally ready and able to take down a fleet of alien warships.
name: Hostile Takeover

description: The epic saga from Homer has influenced literature since the day it was discovered. Presented is a re-telling of the classic epic from the human perspective, rather than from that of the Greek Gods. Covered within the pages are the events that led to the extraordinary Trojan War. Her name was Helen, her beauty was renowned throughout the world. "The face that launched a thousand ships". In this struggle, great human heroes, both in glory and in weakness, grapple in a conflict that raged for ten years. Collects issues 1-4.
name: TPB

description: Volume brings together the never collected material of the “Brain Dead Horror” series which ran within the Vietnam Journal Continuum publication. Featuring reporter 'Journal' impersonating an officer and having to lead the men in combat! This volume also contains two Don Lomax short tales called “Dustoff” and “Zipper Raid”.
name: Book Eight

description: As Supergirl and Superboy battle the Eclipso-infected throngs in Metropolis, Hank Henshaw takes the battle directly into the Hive-Mind controlling them. And Lois & Clark overhear something Lex wishes they hadn't!
name: Chapter Ten

description: Colonel Nick Fury, veteran CIA operative, has been at war for a lifetime. Now he sits alone in a dank hotel room, coughing his confession into a tape recorder, laying out a legacy of carnage stretching back to World War II. Because when that war ended, another one began - and Fury sought it out, regardless of the cost to those who loved him, including loyal George Hatherly, congressman Pug McCuskey and the beautiful Shirley DeFabio. From Indochina to Cuba, Vietnam to Nicaragua, Fury battled across the decades, encountering young Marine sniper Frank Castle and the nightmarish Barracuda - his constant lust for combat blinding him to all other concerns. But the end is coming. The debt is long past due. And Fury's true legacy will soon be written in blood for all to see. Collecting FURY MAX #1-13.
name: HC

volume.name: Fury Max: My War Gone By

description:
With this collection of Sketchbook, Comixburo intends to bring you the very best drawings and sketches from famous artists from all around the world. Perfect tool for the artist to be and perfect comparison for the established drawer whose curious about the depths of his fellow artists. This collection gives a great inside look at the work of the selected artists and provides great 'how to' knowledge to every readers.

This sketchbook features the work of fame French comic artist Olivier Vatine. Sketches inside features some of Vatine's early work, female portraits, head sketches and many more.

This sketchbook features the work of fame French comic Manchu. Sketches inside features some of Manchu's early work, female portraits, head sketches and many more.

Comes in a small and convenient size of 18 by 22 inches, this is a 52 color pages sketchbook.
name: Vol. 2

description:
It’s the giant-sized series finale! There’s a brand new Spandex team – Lipstick, Mr Hard, Pussycat, Grr’nn, Prowler, Super DJ and Liberty! But how will they get on? And where are the old gang? Includes five variant covers (all contained in this issue) by Jeffrey Brown, Warwick Johnson Cadwell, Nigel Dobbyn, T’Sao Wei and Martin Eden.

The comic about an all-gay superteam. The special has several covers all done by guest artists.

name: Der Tag, an dem die Erde blökte!!
Kara Ben Nemsi: In Letzter Minute

description: The carnival that has come to Mystic Falls isn't what it appears to be-and when Sheriff Forbes realizes that people are disappearing, she turns to Damon for help!
name: Circus of Souls Part 1 of 3

description: With Terry's trust in his mentor Bruce Wayne shaken, Dick Grayson and Barbara Gordon reveal the truth about what happenned to the Bat-family all those years ago...
name: Mark of the Phantasm, Part 4 of 7: Older Wounds

description:
Cover: Colin Macneil (Judge Dredd)

  • Droid Life (Cat Sullivan)
  • Judge Dredd – A Night in Sylvia Plath (part 1) (John Wagner - Colin Macneil)
  • Sinister Dexter - The Generican Dream: Congo (part 4 - final part) (Dan Abnett - Jake Lynch)
  • Aquila - Carnifex (part 3) (Gordon Rennie - Leigh Gallagher)
  • Brass Sun - Floating Worlds (part 5) (Ian Edginton - INJ Culbard)
  • Black Shuck (part 2) (Leah Moore and John Reppion - Steve Yeowell)
name: Prog 1892

description: It's the final chapter to Batman's confrontation with the manical Dr. Faceless. Is he a criminal mastermind or merely insane?
name: Doctor Faceless, Part 3 of 3

description: Van de Kasseien has seen the light: he's going to invest in the meat industry. He himself has other meat in his hands on Tenerife and thus Marcel Kiekeboe has to haggle with a bunch of dodo farmers on Texel. But they have no good intentions in mind...
name: Bistro Dodo

description: Alanis takes part in a reality show on television. Suddenly she's a celebrity, including pictures on the cover of magazines and a famous lover. Jens, Fanny's ex, is investigating illegal cigarettes and is put in the line of fire. On top of that, he gets a crush on Tomboy...
name: Geen Rook

description: Marcel searches for an original birthday present for mrs. Van de Kasseien. He ends up at Muribanda, a firm which organizes space travels for rich people. Meanwhile Tomboy gets started on a cruise ship, the Quality Time. She's very secretive however about her mission and Fanny and Jens decide to keep an eye on her. They travel with her as stowaways, which turns sour quickly...
name: Zonder Vuur

description:
The future begins now! Join us as we present pop culture's first hero - Buck Rogers! The first man out of time... the first man to be taken from his present and thrown into the future... the inspiration for countless heroes, and it all begins here!

This volume collects Buck Rogers issues 1-5.
name: Volume 1

description:
The future continues here! Join us once again as we present pop culture's first hero - Buck Rogers! The first man out of time... the first man to be taken from his present and thrown into the future... the inspiration for countless heroes, and it all begins here!

This volume collects: Buck Rogers issues 6-12.
name: Volume 2

volume.name: Buck Rogers: From the Earth To the Moon
